1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses a generalization of the Quicksort algorithm, which is a well-known sorting algorithm studied in the context of data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.AL (Computational Complexity): The paper analyzes the expected cost of the multipivot Quicksort algorithm, which involves studying the time complexity of the algorithm. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with the analysis of a randomized algorithm, which involves techniques from probability theory and discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper may involve information-theoretic concepts in the analysis of the algorithm. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper may involve numerical methods in the analysis of the algorithm, such as Monte Carlo simulations.
